  "prompt": "Add new test suites to the existing hx-icon test file. Read the current test file first, then append the new tests.\n\n## File to modify\n`/Volumes/Development/booked/helix/.worktrees/feature-phase-2-component-implement-hx-icon/packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-icon/hx-icon.test.ts`\n\n## Current test file ends at line 188 with `});`\n\n## Component API to test (relevant to new tests)\n```typescript\n// hx-icon.ts render() method\noverride render() {\n  // Inline fetch mode takes precedence when src is a non-empty string.\n  if (typeof this.src === 'string' && this.src.trim().length > 0) {\n    return this._renderInline();\n  }\n  if (this.name) {\n    return this._renderSprite();\n  }\n  return nothing;\n}\n\n// _sanitizeSvg strips:\n// 1. <script> and <foreignObject> elements\n// 2. on* event-handler attributes on ALL elements (including root svg)\n// 3. javascript: and data: URIs from href/xlink:href/src attributes\n\n@property({ type: String })\nsrc: string | undefined = undefined;\n```\n\n## Tests to add\n\nAppend two new describe blocks INSIDE the outer `describe('hx-icon', () => {` block, just before the final closing `});`.\n\n### 1. `describe('Property: src', ...)` (3 tests)\n\n```\nit('src=\"\" is treated as absent — sprite mode still works', ...)\n  // fixture: '<hx-icon name=\"check\" src=\"\"></hx-icon>'\n  // expect: shadowQuery(el, 'svg[part=\"svg\"]') to be truthy (sprite mode rendered)\n  // expect: el.src === '' (property is empty string)\n\nit('src attribute reflects to src property', ...)\n  // fixture: '<hx-icon src=\"/icons/check.svg\"></hx-icon>'\n  // expect: el.src === '/icons/check.svg'\n  // Note: no fetch is triggered in this test - just property reflection\n\nit('renders nothing while src is set but fetch not yet resolved', ...)\n  // Mock fetch to return a pending promise using vi.fn()\n  // fixture: '<hx-icon src=\"/test.svg\"></hx-icon>'\n  // The _inlineSvg is empty before fetch resolves\n  // expect: shadowQuery(el, '[part=\"svg\"]') to be null (nothing rendered)\n  // Restore fetch after test\n```\n\n### 2. `describe('Sanitizer', ...)` (5 tests)\n\nThese tests call the sanitizer indirectly by mocking fetch to return controlled SVG strings, then awaiting the update.\n\nPattern for each test:\n```typescript\nconst originalFetch = globalThis.fetch;\ntry {\n  globalThis.fetch = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({\n    ok: true,\n    text: async () => '<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">...</svg>',\n  } as Response);\n\n  const el = await fixture<HelixIcon>('<hx-icon src=\"/icon.svg\"></hx-icon>');\n  // Wait for fetch to complete\n  await el.updateComplete;\n  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 50));\n  await el.updateComplete;\n  \n  // query shadow root...\n} finally {\n  globalThis.fetch = originalFetch;\n}\n```\n\nTests:\n1. `strips <script> elements from fetched SVG`\n   - SVG payload: `<svg xmlns=\"...\"  ><script>alert(1)</script><path d=\"M0 0\"/></svg>`\n   - expect: no `<script>` in `el.shadowRoot?.innerHTML`\n\n2. `strips on* event-handler attributes from child elements`\n   - SVG payload: `<svg xmlns=\"...\"><path d=\"M0 0\" onclick=\"alert(1)\"/></svg>`\n   - expect: no element with `onclick` attribute in shadowRoot innerHTML\n\n3. `strips on* event-handler attributes from root svg element`\n   - SVG payload: `<svg xmlns=\"...\" onload=\"alert(1)\"><path d=\"M0 0\"/></svg>`\n   - expect: rendered SVG does not have `onload` attribute\n\n4. `strips javascript: href values`\n   - SVG payload: `<svg xmlns=\"...\"><a href=\"javascript:alert(1)\"><path d=\"M0 0\"/></a></svg>`\n   - expect: no `href=\"javascript:` in shadowRoot innerHTML\n\n5. `strips <foreignObject> elements`\n   - SVG payload: `<svg xmlns=\"...\"><foreignObject><div>XSS</div></foreignObject></svg>`\n   - expect: no `<foreignObject>` in shadowRoot innerHTML\n\n## Imports already present\n- `import { describe, it, expect, afterEach } from 'vitest';`\n- `import { page } from '@vitest/browser/context';`\n- Add `vi` to the vitest imports: `import { describe, it, expect, afterEach, vi } from 'vitest';`\n\n## Important\n- Do NOT use `vi.spyOn` or `vi.mock` — use direct assignment of `globalThis.fetch` with a try/finally restore\n- Always use `await el.updateComplete` plus a short timeout to allow the async fetch to complete\n- Do not test src=undefined (already covered by existing tests)\n- Keep tests simple and deterministic\n\n## Working directory\n`/Volumes/Development/booked/helix/.worktrees/feature-phase-2-component-implement-hx-icon`\n"
